sequenceDiagram
    actor User as 👤 User
    participant Browser as 🌐 Browser
    participant Kong as 🔀 Kong Gateway
    participant Auth as 🔐 Auth Service
    participant Vault as 🔑 HashiCorp Vault
    participant Redis as ⚡ Redis
    participant DB as 🗄️ PostgreSQL
    participant OIDC as 🔑 OIDC Provider<br/>(Google/GitHub)

    Note over User,OIDC: 🔐 OAuth2 / OIDC Login Flow

    User->>Browser: Click "Login with Google"
    Browser->>Kong: GET /auth/oauth/google
    Kong->>Auth: Forward request
    Auth->>Auth: Generate state + PKCE challenge
    Auth->>Redis: SETEX state:{nonce} 300s
    Auth-->>Browser: 302 Redirect → Google OAuth
    Browser->>OIDC: GET /oauth/authorize?client_id=...&state=...
    OIDC->>User: Show consent screen
    User->>OIDC: Grant permissions
    OIDC-->>Browser: 302 Redirect → /auth/callback?code=...&state=...
    Browser->>Kong: GET /auth/callback?code=...
    Kong->>Auth: Forward callback
    Auth->>Redis: GET state:{nonce} — verify state
    Redis-->>Auth: State valid
    Auth->>OIDC: POST /token (exchange code)
    OIDC-->>Auth: id_token + access_token
    Auth->>Auth: Verify id_token signature (JWKS)
    Auth->>DB: UPSERT users (email, provider, sub)
    DB-->>Auth: User record
    Auth->>Vault: GET secret/jwt-signing-key
    Vault-->>Auth: RSA private key
    Auth->>Auth: Sign JWT (RS256, exp: 15min)
    Auth->>Auth: Sign Refresh Token (exp: 7d)
    Auth->>Redis: SETEX refresh:{userId} 7d token_hash
    Auth-->>Browser: Set-Cookie: refresh_token (httpOnly, secure, sameSite=strict)
    Auth-->>Browser: 200 OK — {access_token, expires_in}

    Note over User,OIDC: 🔄 Token Refresh Flow

    Browser->>Kong: POST /auth/refresh (Cookie: refresh_token)
    Kong->>Auth: Forward
    Auth->>Redis: GET refresh:{userId}
    Redis-->>Auth: Token hash match
    Auth->>Vault: GET secret/jwt-signing-key
    Vault-->>Auth: RSA private key
    Auth->>Auth: Issue new access_token (RS256)
    Auth-->>Browser: 200 OK — {access_token}

    Note over User,OIDC: 🛡️ API Request with JWT

    Browser->>Kong: GET /api/orders (Authorization: Bearer <jwt>)
    Kong->>Kong: Verify JWT signature (RS256 public key)
    Kong->>Kong: Check exp, iss, aud claims
    Kong->>Kong: Rate limit by userId
    Kong-->>Browser: 401 if invalid/expired
    Kong->>Auth: Introspect token (optional, cached)
    Auth-->>Kong: Token valid, scopes: [read:orders]
    Kong->>Kong: Inject X-User-ID, X-User-Email headers
    Kong->>Order: Forward with user context
